This should get optimized down to a simple copy. We need to actually construct the value, rather than calling memcpy, to satisfy strict aliasing rules.

Destroy the underlying value.

This should get optimized down to a no-op. We could skip it if we could add a static assert on <em>std::is&#95;trivially&#95;copyable()</em>, but we currently support versions of GCC that don&#39;t understand that.
